      "title": "System Requirements and Workspace Preparation",
      "body": "<!-- HDC_HTML -->\r\n<article>\n<h1>3. System Requirements and Workspace Preparation</h1>\n\n<ol start=\"1\"><li>A Windows development environment with Delphi installed and working.</li></ol>\n<ol start=\"2\"><li>Access to the original VCL source code and form files.</li></ol>\n<ol start=\"3\"><li>A separate target directory for generated FMX output.</li></ol>\n<ol start=\"4\"><li>Sufficient disk space for source, output, reports, and milestone backups.</li></ol>\n<ol start=\"5\"><li>A backup strategy before major converter runs or large rule changes.</li></ol>\n<p>A clean folder layout is strongly recommended. Keep the converter source, the original VCL project, and the converted FMX output in separate locations. This prevents stale output files from being mistaken for current results and makes it much easier to compare source and target artifacts during troubleshooting.</p>\n\n<table class=\"doc-table\">\n<tbody><tr><th>Workspace Area</th><th>Recommended Use</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Converter folder</td><td>Contains the converter source and its own documentation/scripts.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Source project folder</td><td>Contains the original VCL application being migrated.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Output folder</td><td>Contains only the newly generated FMX project for the current run.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Backup storage</td><td>Contains milestone snapshots, cloud copies, or archived converter states.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n</article>",
      "status": "Approved",
      "iconName": "auto",
