    {
      "id": "{F4305DE6-B6FC-41AF-9E24-A1176AE21912}",
      "parentId": "",
      "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
      "body": "# 16. Frequently Asked Questions\r\n\r\n<table class=\"doc-table\">\r\n<tr><th>Question</th><th>Answer</th></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Will every project convert perfectly on the first run?</td><td>No. The converter is powerful, but real-world projects still expose new patterns that may need another global rule.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Should I hand-edit the generated FMX project permanently?</td><td>Only for temporary testing or minor final polish. The real fix should go into the converter whenever the pattern is reusable.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Why do I still need Delphi after conversion?</td><td>Because the generated project still has to be built, run, and validated in the real Delphi environment.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Why are backups important?</td><td>Because converter improvements are cumulative, and known-good milestone states are valuable when comparing behavior or recovering from regressions.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>When should I review visuals?</td><td>After the project loads, compiles, and runs acceptably. Visual polish is usually the last phase.</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>What does blocking issues mean?</td><td>It means the converter found a serious unsupported pattern or rule gap. Generated files may exist, but you should resolve the blocking issue before treating the output as a valid converted project.</td></tr>\r\n</table>",
      "status": "Ready",
      "iconName": "auto",
      "owner": "Auto Import",
      "helpId": "IDH_FREQUENTLY_ASKED_QUESTIONS",
      "language": "en-US",
      "tags": "imported,docx,troubleshooting",
      "conditions": "",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T09:56:24.310Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "{91376BA4-78EA-4823-A53A-7524C0884BEC}",
      "parentId": "",
      "title": "Appendix A. Quick Start Checklist",
      "body": "# Appendix A. Quick Start Checklist\r\n\r\n1. Build the converter.\r\n2. Choose source and target folders.\r\n3. Use a clean output directory.\r\n4. Run conversion.\r\n5. Open the FMX project in Delphi.\r\n6. Build, run, and validate the converted app.\r\n7. Improve the converter globally and regenerate as needed.",
      "status": "Ready",
      "iconName": "auto",
      "owner": "Auto Import",
      "helpId": "IDH_APPENDIX_A_QUICK_START_CHECKLIST",
      "language": "en-US",
      "tags": "imported,docx,procedure",
      "conditions": "",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T09:56:24.310Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "{ED82FFA8-2CE8-4915-8CBE-081DEE872077}",
      "parentId": "",
      "title": "Appendix B. Pre-Conversion Checklist",
      "body": "# Appendix B. Pre-Conversion Checklist\r\n\r\n1. Confirm the real source root folder.\r\n2. Confirm the target output folder is correct and clean.\r\n3. Know which workflows are critical in the original application.\r\n4. Ensure supporting files such as databases or media are available for runtime testing.\r\n5. Plan where milestone backups will be stored.",
      "status": "Ready",
      "iconName": "auto",
      "owner": "Auto Import",
      "helpId": "IDH_APPENDIX_B_PRE_CONVERSION_CHECKLIST",
      "language": "en-US",
      "tags": "imported,docx",
      "conditions": "",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T09:56:24.311Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "{90E1CB0C-A14D-4A07-B80B-09CCBE100F2C}",
      "parentId": "",
      "title": "Appendix C. Post-Conversion Review Checklist",
      "body": "# Appendix C. Post-Conversion Review Checklist\r\n\r\n1. Did the forms open without reader errors?\r\n2. Did the project compile on the first pass?\r\n3. Did the application start and close normally?\r\n4. Did core workflows run correctly?\r\n5. Are the remaining issues structural, runtime, or merely visual?\r\n6. Was the converter fixed globally if a reusable defect was found?",
      "status": "Ready",
      "iconName": "auto",
      "owner": "Auto Import",
      "helpId": "IDH_APPENDIX_C_POST_CONVERSION_REVIEW_CHECKLIST",
      "language": "en-US",
